    "This mechanism not only prevents illegal states but also simulates a realistic robotic behavior where joints can rotate endlessly in one direction.1 if joint_angle > joint_upper_limit: 2 joint_angle = joint_lower_limitThis action space design provides a clear, understandable framework for the robot's movements, facilitating the learning model's exploration and exploitation of the environment.",
    "The discrete nature of the actions, combined with the fixed movement increments, allows for a straightforward mapping between actions and outcomes, aids the learning process.1 self.action_space = spaces.Discrete(64)• Reward: We use the same reward function as explained in 4.3.3.",
    "ConclusionThis chapter presented an approach for estimating the WCET of real-time robotic algorithms.",
    "By utilizing collision detection algorithms with two case studies, the 6-DOF robotic arm and a system involving two mobile cylinders and a stationary box, we explored methods that address the challenges in measuring WCET.We introduced the use of GA as a search-based method for exploring vast input spaces, guided by fitness functions aimed at maximizing execution time and diversity.",
    "Specific configurations and genetic operators tailored to each case study were discussed."
